The paper discusses local explanation methods for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning, computer vision, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the lower level features of a DNN, which suggests a focus on neural networks and their architecture, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper discusses the visual and quantitative similarity of the explanations produced by DNNs with randomly-initialized weights and those with learned weights, which suggests a potential focus on natural language processing and computational linguistics, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
